                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-742" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY GUY.</persName>
                  </hi> I live at Kingston, in Surrey. On 29th Nov., at a quarter past nine o'clock, I left my horse and chaise in care of West—I left a cloak in the chaise—this produced is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471213-name-743" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-743" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-743" type="surname" value="WEST"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-743" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY WEST.</persName>
                  </hi> I am horsekeeper at the Falcon, at Kingston. About nine o'clock that night the prosecutor told me to put a cloth on his horse—I then saw a cloak in the chaise—I doubled it up, and laid it on the cushion—when I came back with the cloth it was gone.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
